  <h1 id="title"><b>Berserk</b></h1>
  <p id="sub">The manga that changed everything</p>
  
  <figure id="img-div">
    <img id="image" src="https://external-content.duckduckgo.com/iu/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fpavbca.com%2Fwalldb%2Foriginal%2F7%2F8%2F7%2F17580.jpg&f=1&nofb=1" alt="Guts, the main character from Berserk"/>
    <figcaption id="img-caption">
 <i> Berserk</i> is a Japanese manga series written and illustrated by Kentaro Miura which began in 1989 published by <i>Monthly Animal House</i> then moved to <i>Young Animal</i> in 1992 where the series has remained since.
    </figcaption>
  <figcaption id="img-caption">
    <i>Berserk</i> is a seinen manga set in a dark fantasy, medieval world. Its plot follows the protagonist, Guts, dubbed the "black swordsman", and his indoctrination into the "Band of the Hawk", a mercenary group led by Griffith, a driven man who vows to have his own kingdom. With these two and many other important characters, <i>Berserk</i> is as much a gritty, high-fantasy epic as it is a thematic dissection of free will, destiny, human struggle, and trauma. 
  <figcaption id="img-caption">
   <i> Berserk</i> is regarded as one of the greatest manga of all time, in particular it has been praised for its story, influence, and Miura's art style. With over 50 million copies sold worldwide as of 2022 and a vast, dedicated fanbase, <i>Berserk</i> has retained its legendary status after all these years. However, in May 2021 the series' creator, Kentaro Miura, unexpectedly passed away, he was 54. As one of the most renowned manga authors and artists, his legacy lives on eternally, so much so that serialization of <i>Berserk</i> has continued as of June 2022. 
   </figcaption>
   <img src="https://external-content.duckduckgo.com/iu/?u=https%3A%2F%2Fgamersunite.mx%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F05%2FKentaro-Miura.jpg&f=1&nofb=1" alt="Kentaro Miura, author of Berserk" style="margin:auto">
<p>You can read more about Kentaro Miura and his life  <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kentaro_Miura" target="_blank">here.</a><p/>
 </figure>
